The first command line arguement you must provide is the drive which you wish to install Arch on. you can find this by running fdisk -l and providing its name in the same format that
the output of fdisk -l gives you. Do: /dev/sdXX Don't: sdXX

The second command line arguement you must provide is your username. This MUST BE all lowercase with no whitespaces. Do: banana Don't: ban ana

The third command line arguement you must provide is your password. It is what you will use to login don't mess it up

Connect to the internet via "iwctl"> "station list"> "station connect [your network name here]"> verify it is connected in the station list menu> "exit" 
Verify with a simple ping to google.com via "ping google.com"